com.paydiant.android.ui.service.gcm

Class GCMUtilityServiceListenerAdapter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.paydiant.android.ui.service.gcm.GCMUtilityServiceListenerAdapter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IGCMUtilityServiceListener

    public class GCMUtilityServiceListenerAdapter
extends Object
implements IGCMUtilityServiceListener
    This class provides an empty implementation for IGCMUtilityServiceListener. Any classes that wants to use only a subset of the listener methods can override the relevant methods and use it as the interface implementation. 

     GCMUtilityServiceListenerAdapter gcmUtilityServiceListenerAdapter = new GCMUtilityServiceListenerAdapter() {
 
    @Override
    public void onRegistrationSuccess(String registrationId) {
    }
 
    @Override
    public void onGCMUtilityServiceError(PaydiantException e) {
    }
 };
 igcmUtilityService.setListener(gcmUtilityServiceListenerAdapter);
    Note: App developers are encouraged to use the ListenerAdapter implementations whenever possible as the Listener interfaces might get updated with new functionality/methods from one SDK release to the other. Therefore using a ListenerAdapter will make sure that there wont be any compilation issues due to unimplemented methods during a SDK upgrade.

    Since:
    4.5.0.1
